# Module 02 Study Notes — Incident Classification

## Key Takeaways

1. **Always map to MITRE ATT&CK** — it creates a common language across teams and tools.
2. **VERIS Actor-Action-Asset-Attribute** is great for reporting up to management.
3. **Metadata is evidence** — timestamps, IPs, hashes must be exact and timestamped in UTC.
4. **One incident can have multiple techniques** — don't stop at the first match.

## MITRE ATT&CK Memory Aid (Tactics in Order)

```
"Really Clever Adversaries Exploit People's Defenses & Create Lots of Extraordinary Impact"
  R     C    A      E       P    D        C     L     E      I
Recon  Dev  Access Exec  Persist Priv-Esc Evade Cred  Disco  Lateral  Collect  C2  Exfil  Impact
```

## Enrichment Checklist

- [ ] Looked up IP on VirusTotal / AbuseIPDB
- [ ] Checked file hash on VirusTotal
- [ ] Checked URL in URLscan.io / URLhaus
- [ ] Verified email headers with MXToolBox
- [ ] Searched hash/IP in AlienVault OTX
- [ ] Cross-referenced MITRE ATT&CK

## TheHive Case Classification Fields

```
Title:         [CATEGORY] Brief description
TLP:           WHITE / GREEN / AMBER / RED
PAP:           WHITE / GREEN / AMBER / RED
Severity:      Low / Medium / High / Critical
Tags:          [mitre:T1566] [type:phishing] [status:active]
```

